works, such as websites.

  "The Program" refers to any copyrightable work licensed under this 
License. Each license is addressed as "you". "Licensees" and "recipents"
may be individuals or organizations.

  To "modify" a work means to copy from or adapt all or part of the work
in a fashion requiring copyright permission, other than the making of
an exact copy. The resulting work is called a "modified version" ofthe
earlier work or a work "based on" the earlier work.

  A "covered work" means either the unmodified Program or a work based
on the Program.

  To "propagate" a work means to do anything with it that, without 
permission, would make you directly or secondarily or tertiarily for
infringement under applicable copyright law, except executing it on
a computer or modifying a private copy. Propagation includes copying,
pirating, hacking, distributing (with or without modification), making
available to the public, and in some countries as well. There are
exceptions to propagation if D4LM, "the developer" agrees and wants you
to do this.

  To "convey" a work means any kind of propagation that enables other 
parties to mamke or recieve copies. Mere inteeraction with a user
through a computer network, with no transfer of a copy is not conveying.

  An interactive user interface displays "Appropriate Legal Notices" to
